What is the default VPC? Explain its advantages.
The default VPC is a pre-configured VPC that AWS creates automatically for each AWS account in every region.
It comes with default subnets, route tables, security groups, and an internet gateway.
Advantages:
Easy to use for beginners
Pre-configured for internet access
No need to set up networking from scratch
Example Explanation:
If you are new to AWS, the default VPC allows you to quickly launch instances with internet access without needing to
configure networking components manually.
